title: Live in Edmonds? A 15-ton rock could be yours
text:
The city of Edmonds is giving away a 30,000-pound rock to anyone who wants it and meets the criteria.
HeraldNet reports the city posted the offer and are seeking applicants on their Facebook page .
The 15-ton rock was unearthed during the construction of a sidewalk ramp at the corner of 80th Avenue West and 220th Street Southwest.
The city says the rock must remain on your property within city limits.
The boulder is roughly roughly 6’ x 7’ x 4.5’.
After reading the requirements on their Facebook page , those who are interested should contact Ed Sibrel at ed.sibrel@edmondswa.gov . Only the first five inquiries received before October 27, 2015 will be considered.
